Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 11/2017]
Title: INTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: LOWER INSTRUMENT PANEL: INSTALLATION; 2016 - 2017 MY Prius [11/2015 - 11/2017]

INSTALLATION

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL LOWER INSTRUMENT PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) When installing a new lower instrument panel assembly, No. 1 instrument panel sub-assembly or lower instrument panel sub-assembly:

(1) Immediately before installing the lower instrument panel assembly, twist and cut off the portion as shown in the illustration.

(b) Install the lower instrument panel sub-assembly with the 2 bolts <A>, 4 bolts <B>, 3 screws <C> or <G> and screw <D>.

*a

Bolt <A>

*b

Bolt <B>

*c

Screw <C> or <G>

*d

Screw <D>

*e

Clip

-

-

NOTICE:

  • Do not damage the lower instrument panel sub-assembly.
  • Do not allow the wire harnesses to interfere with the surrounding parts.
  • If a screw <C> is loose and cannot be installed securely, replace it with a screw <G>.

Torque:

Bolt <A> :

20 N·m {204 kgf·cm, 15 ft·lbf}

Bolt <B> :

13 N·m {133 kgf·cm, 10 ft·lbf}

(c) Install the 2 clips.

(d) Engage each clamp.

*A

w/ Telematics Transceiver

*B

w/ Satellite Radio

(e) Connect each connector.

(f) Engage the 2 claws to connect the cooler (room temp. sensor) thermistor as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(g) Engage the 4 clips and 2 claws to connect the lower instrument cover sub-assembly to the upper steering column cover.

3. INSTALL GLOVE BOX LIGHT ASSEMBLY

4. INSTALL NO. 2 INSTRUMENT PANEL REGISTER ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 4 clips to install the No. 2 instrument panel register assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

5. INSTALL NO. 1 INSTRUMENT PANEL REGISTER ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 4 clips to install the No. 1 instrument panel register assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

6. INSTALL NO. 2 LOWER INSTRUMENT PANEL FINISH PANEL

(a) Engage the 9 clips to install the No. 2 lower instrument panel finish panel as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

7. INSTALL SHIFT LEVER HOLE COVER

(a) Connect each connector

(b) Engage the 5 clips to install the shift lever hole cover as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(c) Engage the clamp.

8. INSTALL LOWER CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Connect each connector

(b) Engage each clamp.

(c) Engage the 5 clips to install the lower center instrument cluster finish panel sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

9. INSTALL GLOVE COMPARTMENT DOOR STOPPER SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the claw to install the glove compartment door stopper sub-assembly.

10. INSTALL GLOVE COMPARTMENT DOOR ASSEMBLY

(a) Hold the glove compartment door assembly at an angle approximately 64.2° from its closed position and engage the 2 hinges horizontally as shown in the illustration.

*a

64.2°

-

-

Install in this Direction

-

-

NOTICE:

Engaging the hinges from an upward angle will deform the hinges. Be sure to install the glove compartment door assembly horizontally.

(b) Slightly bend the stoppers (A) and (B) in the directions indicated by the arrows shown in the illustration and engage the stoppers to install the glove compartment door assembly.

*1

Glove Compartment Door Stopper Sub-assembly

(c) Engage the claw to connect the glove compartment door stopper sub-assembly.

11. INSTALL NO. 2 INSTRUMENT PANEL UNDER COVER SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Connect the connector.

(b) Engage the 2 guides as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(c) Engage the 3 claws to install the No. 2 instrument panel under cover sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction
